Melania Trump, the First Lady of the United States, will be joining her husband, President Donald Trump, on a foreign trip. The trip will last for eight days and include stops in Saudi Arabia, Israel, Rome, Brussels, and Sicily. Melania will participate in her own events and will also attend spousal programs at the NATO and G-7 summits. She will conclude the trip by delivering remarks to US military personnel and families in Italy. Melania expressed her excitement about the trip and her intention to speak with women and children from different countries. The White House will provide daily guidance and a full readout of Melania's activities will be provided at the end of each day.